I have the same issue in v1.9. In my case, I am trying to get a .tflite model to serve from Firebase.
The other method I tried (which has been mentioned above) is creating a SavedModel then attempting to convert using
tf.contrib.lite.TocoConverter.from_saved_model(path_to_savedModel)
but then I get a different error:
ValueError: Tensors input_example_tensor:0 not known type tf.string

body:
I have the same issue in v1.9. In my case, I am trying to get a .tflite model to serve from Firebase.
The other method I tried (which has been mentioned above) is creating a SavedModel then attempting to convert using 
`tf.contrib.lite.TocoConverter.from_saved_model(path_to_savedModel)`
but then I get a different error:
**ValueError: Tensors input_example_tensor:0 not known type tf.string**
